BBVA Bolsters Retail Division For Growth Abroad, Expansion Says

-- B y   C h a r l e s   P e n t y
-- 
2011-06-06T05:35:35Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-06/bbva-bolsters-retail-division-for-growth-abroad-expansion-says.html
Banco Bilbao Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  is
reorganizing its retail banking business and hiring executives
from other banks as it seeks growth abroad, Expansion reported.  The bank has hired people including Fernando Morillo,
previously head of retail banking at Bankinter SA, and Domingo
Caamano, formerly head of BMW Bank GmbH in Spain, and plans to
make further appointments as it bolsters its Global Retail and
Business Banking division, the newspaper said, without saying
where it got the information.  As part of its growth plans, BBVA is in talks over
strategic alliances in  China  in private banking and payments
businesses, the newspaper said.
